# Trivy ignore file
# Suppress findings that are acceptable for this project

# KSV001 - Process can elevate its own privileges (allowPrivilegeEscalation)
# Already set to false in all containers. Trivy flags the redis container
# which uses a specific base image that sets this at runtime.
AVD-KSV-0001

# KSV003 - Default capabilities not dropped for system containers
AVD-KSV-0003

# KSV011 - CPU limits not set (set per container, Trivy may flag init containers)
AVD-KSV-0011

# KSV014 - Root file system not set to read-only for redis (redis needs /data writable)
AVD-KSV-0014

# KSV020 - Runs as root (redis uses numeric UID 999, non-root)
AVD-KSV-0020

# KSV021 - Runs as root group
AVD-KSV-0021
